Sweet Potato-and-Red Lentil Curry
http://www.cookinglight.com/recipes/sweet-potato-and-red-lentil-curry
Active Time: 15 Mins
Total Time: 8 Hours 15 Mins
Serves 4

2 c peeled, cubed sweet potato (about 1 medium)
1 3/4 c water, divided
1 c dried red lentils
1 c low-sodium fat-free vegetable broth
1/2 c finely chopped white onion
1.5 Tbsp Thai red curry paste (such as Thai Kitchen)
1 tsp garam masala
1 tsp grated peeled fresh ginger
1 tsp ground turmeric
Cooking spray
1 1/2 tsp sugar, divided
3/8 tsp kosher salt
2 garlic cloves, minced
3 oz c tomato paste
1/2 c canned light coconut milk
1/4 c apple cider vinegar
1/2 c very thinly sliced red onion
2 c hot cooked brown rice
1/2 c fresh cilantro leaves 

Place sweet potato, 1.5 cups water, and next 7 ingredients (through turmeric)
in a 5- to 6-quart electric slow cooker coated with cooking spray. Add 1/2
tsp sugar, salt, garlic, and tomato paste; stir well to combine. Cover and
cook on low 8 hours. Turn off heat; stir in coconut milk. Let stand, covered,
5 minutes.

Combine remaining 1/4 cup water, remaining 1 tsp sugar, and vinegar in a
microwave-safe bowl; microwave at high 2 minutes or until boiling. Add onion
to vinegar mixture; let stand 20 minutes at room temperature. Drain.

Place 1/2 cup rice in each of 8 shallow bowls. Top each serving with 1 1/4 c
lentil mixture, 2 Tbsp red onion mixture, and 2 Tbsp cilantro.
